{{Not to be confused with|May 17|qq=May 17}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月十七|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 17일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 17''' is the 17th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 18th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1641|1641]] [[:en:June 25|June 25]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate relocated Dutch residents from Hirado to the artificial island of [[:en:Dejima|Dejima]] in Nagasaki. * [[:en:Bunka|Bunka]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1809|1809]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – [[:en:Mamiya Rinzō|Mamiya Rinzō]] crossed alone to Sakhalin, proving that it was indeed an island; the strait was thereafter named the [[:en:Strait of Tartary|Mamiya Kaikyō]]. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1870|1870]] [[:en:June 15|June 15]]) – Tondenhei colonists began to settle Hokkaidō.
== Births == * [[:en:Kanbun (era)|Kanbun]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1668|1668]] [[:en:June 26|June 26]]) – {{ill|Amamori Hōshū|ja|雨森芳洲|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amamori Hōshū|qq=}}, a Confucian scholar (died [[:en:1755|1755]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1865|1865]] [[:en:June 10|June 10]]) – [[:en:Murakami Kijo|Murakami Onikijō]], a haiku poet (died [[:en:1938|1938]]). * 慶応1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1865, June 10) – [[:en:Koizumi Matajirō|Koizumi Matashirō]], a politician (died [[:en:1951|1951]]). * 慶応2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1866|1866]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – [[:en:Takakusu Junjiro|Kōkusun Junjirō]], a Buddhist scholar (died [[:en:1945|1945]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Huangchu|Huangchu]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:226|226]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – [[:en:Cao Pi|Cao Pi]] (Wen Emperor), the first Emperor of Wei in the Three Kingdoms period, and son of [[:en:Cao Cao|Cao Cao]] (born [[:en:187|187]]). * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/An'ei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 安永 (元号)}} 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1778|1778]] [[:en:June 11|June 11]]) – {{ill|Nagaya Sōen|ja|永谷宗円|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaya Sōen|qq=}}, a village headman and developer of the blue-steeped sencha brewing method (born [[:en:1681|1681]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1839|1839]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – {{ill|Kozeki Sanei|ja|小関三英|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kozeki Sanei|qq=}}, a physician and Rangaku scholar (born [[:en:1787|1787]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:July 6|July 6]]) – [[:en:Harada Sanosuke|Harada Sano-suke]], a member of the [[:en:Shinsengumi|新選組]] (birth year unknown).
